    "body": "## Purpose\r\nThe flashinfer trtllm allreduce backend does not work for multi-node setup (See issue https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/issues/2006). As a result, running allreduce fusion results in hang in multi-node. This PR resolves this by auto-selecting mnnvl backend for flashinfer all reduce in multi-node setup. In single node setup, the default backend remains trtllm due to issue #35772\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\nTest with nvidia/DeepSeek-R1-NVFP4 on the following setup:\r\n1 x GB300 Node - single-node TP4\r\n2 x GB300 Node - multi-node TP8\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\nsingle-node TP4:\r\n```\r\nvllm serve nvidia/DeepSeek-R1-NVFP4 --no-enable-prefix-caching \\\r\n  --tensor-parallel-size 8 \r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n[flashinfer_all_reduce.py:109] Auto-selected flashinfer allreduce backend: trtllm\r\n[flashinfer_all_reduce.py:149] Initialized FlashInfer Allreduce norm fusion workspace with backend=trtllm\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\r\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\r\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9538|±  |0.0058|\r\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9538|±  |0.0058|\r\n```\r\n\r\nmulti-node TP8:\r\n```\r\nbash \"$HOME/vllm/examples/online_serving/multi-node-serving.sh\" \\\r\n    leader \\\r\n    --ray_port=6379 \\\r\n    --ray_cluster_size=2 && \\\r\n  vllm serve nvidia/DeepSeek-R1-NVFP4 --no-enable-prefix-caching \\\r\n  --tensor-parallel-size 8 \\\r\n  --distributed-executor-backend ray\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n[flashinfer_all_reduce.py:109] Auto-selected flashinfer allreduce backend: mnnvl\r\n[flashinfer_all_reduce.py:149] Initialized FlashInfer Allreduce norm fusion workspace with backend=mnnvl\r\n[flashinfer_all_reduce.py:177] Flashinfer allreduce quantization fusion is not supported for multi-node allreduce. Disabling quant fusion.\r\n[allreduce_rms_fusion.py:791] Failed to initialize Flashinfer allreduce workspace. Flashinfer allreduce-norm-quant fusion will be disabled.\r\n```\r\n```\r\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\r\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\r\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9568|±  |0.0056|\r\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9568|±  |0.0056|\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\r\n\r\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\r\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\r\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\r\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\r\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n",
